WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.568 --> 00:00:04.537
<i>Since 1970. the Federal
Witness Protection Program</i>

2
00:00:04.604 --> 00:00:06.765
<i>has relocated
thousands of witnesses.</i>

3
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:08.535
<i>some criminal. some not.</i>

4
00:00:08.608 --> 00:00:10.735
<i>to neighborhoods
all across the country.</i>

5
00:00:10.810 --> 00:00:13.404
<i>Every one of those individuals
shares a unique attribute</i>

6
00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:16.711
<i>distinguishing them from the
rest of the general population.</i>

7
00:00:16.783 --> 00:00:19.946
<i>And that is.
somebody wants them dead.</i>

8
00:00:36.603 --> 00:00:39.163
<i>Me and you
and you and me</i>

9
00:00:39.239 --> 00:00:41.673
<i>No matter how we
tossed the dice</i>

10
00:00:41.741 --> 00:00:42.901
<i>It had to be</i>

11
00:00:42.976 --> 00:00:44.307
What?
Nothing.

12
00:00:44.377 --> 00:00:46.072
Keep your
eyes on the road. you.

13
00:00:46.146 --> 00:00:47.943
You two are
making me car sick.

14
00:00:48.014 --> 00:00:49.675
Oh. yeah? I can't wait
until you have kids

15
00:00:49.749 --> 00:00:52.377
and they think you're
a ridiculous old fool.

16
00:00:52.452 --> 00:00:55.114
Sorry to ruin your fun
but I'm not having kids.

17
00:00:55.188 --> 00:00:57.622
What? The world's
already overpopulated.

18
00:00:57.690 --> 00:00:59.157
You bite your tongue.

19
00:00:59.225 --> 00:01:02.251
You're giving me
grandbabies. Or else.

20
00:01:02.328 --> 00:01:04.125
Or else what?

21
00:01:04.197 --> 00:01:07.291
Or else I'll have to have
some more babies of my own.

22
00:01:10.336 --> 00:01:11.826
Why are we stopping?

23
00:01:11.905 --> 00:01:14.567
Well. Petey's sick.
And I promised Dominick

24
00:01:14.641 --> 00:01:17.405
I'd drop off
some stuff for him.

25
00:01:17.477 --> 00:01:18.910
All right.

26
00:01:18.978 --> 00:01:22.072
Try and hurry. because if not.
we don't get a good spot. Frank.

27
00:01:22.148 --> 00:01:25.083
Don't worry. I'll just
be a minute. Not even.

28
00:01:29.055 --> 00:01:31.421
Tell Petey I hope
he feels better.

29
00:01:31.491 --> 00:01:33.721
Will do.

30
00:01:33.793 --> 00:01:35.385
And you.
Don't screw with me.

31
00:01:35.462 --> 00:01:37.327
You're going to give me
grandchildren. you hear me?

32
00:01:37.397 --> 00:01:38.386
Yes. Mom.

33
00:01:38.465 --> 00:01:39.762
That's right.

34
00:01:41.835 --> 00:01:43.700
Oh. God.

35
00:01:44.771 --> 00:01:48.298
How does that fat bastard get up
and down those stairs every day?

36
00:01:52.712 --> 00:01:53.736
Who is it?

37
00:01:53.813 --> 00:01:54.837
It's Captain Kangaroo.

38
00:01:54.914 --> 00:01:55.972
Frankie. is that you?

39
00:01:56.049 --> 00:01:59.678
Yeah. yeah. It's Frankie. Come on.
Come on. I'm in a hurry. Petey.

40
00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:03.453
Yo. Frankie!

41
00:02:03.523 --> 00:02:07.653
Hey. Petey. I got a delivery for
you from Dominick.

42
00:02:07.727 --> 00:02:09.422
Oh. yeah?
Yeah.

43
00:02:21.774 --> 00:02:23.105
Petey?

44
00:02:24.577 --> 00:02:26.169
Where are you?

45
00:02:27.914 --> 00:02:29.711
Are you dead?

46
00:02:31.951 --> 00:02:33.248
Oh. no.

47
00:02:40.960 --> 00:02:42.791
Oh. my...

48
00:02:45.698 --> 00:02:47.563
I have no idea
how that happened.

49
00:02:49.402 --> 00:02:52.633
Stand clear! Police.
All right. move it back.

50
00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:13.687
<i>All aboard the southwest
train service to Los Angeles.</i>

51
00:03:13.760 --> 00:03:16.422
<i>With stops
in Dallas. Flagstaff...</i>

52
00:03:17.597 --> 00:03:19.030
<i>Now boarding.</i>

53
00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:23.460
It is so
beyond retarded.

54
00:03:23.536 --> 00:03:26.164
First of all.
we don't say retarded anymore.

55
00:03:31.244 --> 00:03:33.769
Don't even think
about parking there.

56
00:03:33.846 --> 00:03:35.609
U.S. Marshals.

57
00:03:35.682 --> 00:03:38.242
The car better be
here when we get back.

58
00:03:40.920 --> 00:03:43.411
And second. it's not
retarded. It's marketing.

59
00:03:43.489 --> 00:03:44.979
Then. it's retarded marketing.

60
00:03:45.058 --> 00:03:46.582
Look. Imagery
and metaphor...

61
00:03:46.659 --> 00:03:47.819
Oh. thank God.

62
00:03:48.828 --> 00:03:50.386
Hey. What's up?

63
00:03:50.463 --> 00:03:53.432
It seems your sister would prefer
someone else pick her up.

64
00:03:53.499 --> 00:03:55.364
What? Put her on.

65
00:03:55.435 --> 00:03:57.335
Mary would like a word.

66
00:03:58.371 --> 00:03:59.360
Hey.

67
00:03:59.439 --> 00:04:01.498
Don't "hey" me. What the hell
do you think you're doing?

68
00:04:01.574 --> 00:04:04.475
Nothing. But there's no way in
hell I'm taking a ride from some

69
00:04:04.544 --> 00:04:07.707
Rico Suave wannabe
I've never even seen before.

70
00:04:07.780 --> 00:04:09.270
<i>BRANDl.: Why can't
you pick me up?</i>

71
00:04:09.349 --> 00:04:12.375
Because I'm working. All the way
on the other side of town.

72
00:04:12.452 --> 00:04:14.147
<i>But I'm your sister.</i>

73
00:04:14.220 --> 00:04:16.814
Hey. You know what? You can either
accept my friend's generous offer

74
00:04:16.889 --> 00:04:18.356
or start walking.

75
00:04:18.424 --> 00:04:19.652
<i>Fine. I'll take the ride.</i>

76
00:04:19.726 --> 00:04:21.387
You do that.

77
00:04:22.195 --> 00:04:23.287
Here.

78
00:04:25.498 --> 00:04:26.487
Problems?

79
00:04:26.566 --> 00:04:28.193
Brandi got in
this morning.

80
00:04:28.268 --> 00:04:30.327
For my surprise
party. no doubt.

81
00:04:30.403 --> 00:04:33.338
My condolences.
Now. as I was saying.

82
00:04:33.406 --> 00:04:37.137
Imagery and metaphor have been
used to sell products forever.

83
00:04:37.210 --> 00:04:38.802
Please. Jesus.
Take me. now.

84
00:04:38.878 --> 00:04:40.971
Take the Ford Mustang
for instance.

85
00:04:41.047 --> 00:04:43.481
Named for a powerful.
agile animal.

86
00:04:43.549 --> 00:04:47.144
Qualities we also seek in an
automobile. It's called transference.

87
00:04:47.220 --> 00:04:48.983
Yeah. Okay.
What about my Probe?

88
00:04:49.055 --> 00:04:51.148
Exactly what image is
that supposed to transfer?

89
00:04:51.224 --> 00:04:54.421
Because all I'm getting is paper
dress.metal stirrups and legs akimbo.

90
00:04:54.494 --> 00:04:57.429
Exactly what was the thought
process behind that marketing coup?

91
00:04:57.497 --> 00:05:01.433
Say. Bob. What's a metaphor for an
invasive. somewhat humiliating procedure?

92
00:05:01.501 --> 00:05:05.995
Because we really need something
to compete with the Chevy Speculum.

93
00:05:06.072 --> 00:05:08.302
God. why am I
eating this crap?

94
00:05:08.374 --> 00:05:10.774
You going to be
like this all day?

95
00:05:10.843 --> 00:05:11.867
What?
Like...

96
00:05:13.012 --> 00:05:14.104
You know.

97
00:05:14.180 --> 00:05:16.705
I guess it depends how long
it's going to be my birthday.

98
00:05:16.783 --> 00:05:18.683
All day.
There you go.

99
00:05:23.089 --> 00:05:24.351
Here we go.

100
00:05:30.763 --> 00:05:32.663
<i>It's a common
misconception that membership</i>

101
00:05:32.732 --> 00:05:34.199
<i>in the fraternity
of good fellas</i>

102
00:05:34.267 --> 00:05:36.030
<i>is a prerequisite for
admission into</i>

103
00:05:36.102 --> 00:05:38.593
<i>the Federal Witness
Protection Program.</i>

104
00:05:40.273 --> 00:05:41.934
<i>God. If only that were true.</i>

105
00:05:46.045 --> 00:05:47.740
<i>Many witnesses
are everyday folk.</i>

106
00:05:47.814 --> 00:05:49.645
<i>who. through no criminal
enterprise of their own.</i>

107
00:05:49.716 --> 00:05:53.152
<i>have come to possess damning info
about some very dangerous people.</i>

108
00:05:53.219 --> 00:05:57.519
<i>These unlucky losers are trouble magnets.
and should be avoided whenever possible.</i>

109
00:05:57.590 --> 00:05:58.852
Thanks.

110
00:05:58.925 --> 00:05:59.914
Uh-huh.

111
00:05:59.992 --> 00:06:03.325
<i>Which. in my line of work
is almost never.</i>

112
00:06:03.396 --> 00:06:06.024
A ticket?
Are you kidding me?

113
00:06:06.099 --> 00:06:08.431
The car's still there.
ain't it?

114
00:06:08.501 --> 00:06:09.695
Ass-wipe.

115
00:06:09.769 --> 00:06:12.135
It's all right. We'll take
care of you. You're safe.

116
00:06:12.205 --> 00:06:14.833
So. this is how we're
transporting witnesses now?

117
00:06:14.907 --> 00:06:15.965
It's a metaphor.

118
00:06:16.042 --> 00:06:17.942
Oh. yeah? For what? Crap?
Let's go. Go on.

119
00:06:19.545 --> 00:06:21.172
You're welcome.

120
00:06:40.199 --> 00:06:42.190
So. welcome to Albuquerque.
Is this your first time?

121
00:06:42.268 --> 00:06:45.101
<i>Da. Uh. yes.</i>

122
00:06:45.171 --> 00:06:47.139
How long you
been in the States?

123
00:06:47.206 --> 00:06:49.834
Three years. In New York.

124
00:06:49.909 --> 00:06:54.369
Well. this is a far cry from
Manhattan. And a universe from Moscow.

125
00:06:54.447 --> 00:06:55.937
I am from Kiev.

126
00:07:00.019 --> 00:07:01.987
You speak Russian.

127
00:07:02.054 --> 00:07:06.821
A little. I learned it in the eighties
when you guys were still Commies.

128
00:07:06.893 --> 00:07:09.953
In Ukraine.
we speak Ukrainian.

129
00:07:10.029 --> 00:07:11.326
Um...

130
00:07:13.633 --> 00:07:14.827
Shut up.

131
00:07:17.069 --> 00:07:18.127
<i>Hi. Stan.</i>

132
00:07:18.204 --> 00:07:19.398
Hi. Mary. It's Stan.

133
00:07:19.472 --> 00:07:21.406
I know it's you. Stan.
That's why I said. "Hi. Stan. "

134
00:07:21.474 --> 00:07:23.635
Oh. Right. So did
you pick up the witness?

135
00:07:23.709 --> 00:07:25.370
Yeah. we're on the way
to the apartment now.

136
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:28.346
Listen. I just got a call
from Albuquerque PD and. uh...

137
00:07:28.414 --> 00:07:29.472
<i>Oh. boy.</i>

138
00:07:29.549 --> 00:07:30.743
"And. uh. oh. boy"
what. Stan?

139
00:07:30.817 --> 00:07:32.444
I know that tone.
Something happened.

140
00:07:32.518 --> 00:07:35.419
Yeah. Frankie Santoro's kid might
have been shot last night.

141
00:07:35.488 --> 00:07:37.217
What? Where? Is he dead?

142
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:39.417
I said "might."
all right? Might.

143
00:07:39.492 --> 00:07:42.256
They found a body on one of those
development sites out the Pan Am Freeway.

144
00:07:42.328 --> 00:07:43.386
I'm on my way.

145
00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:46.261
That's one choice. But bringing a witness
to the murder site of another witness

146
00:07:46.332 --> 00:07:49.392
<i>violates at least
six codes of conduct.</i>

147
00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:51.528
I know what you're doing. You're
holding the phone out the window.

148
00:07:51.604 --> 00:07:53.071
Stan. I can't hear you!
You're breaking up!

149
00:07:53.139 --> 00:07:54.970
She's holding the phone out the
window. Mary. you listen to me.

150
00:07:55.041 --> 00:07:56.474
Stan?

151
00:07:56.542 --> 00:07:58.305
<i>I absolutely...</i>

152
00:07:58.377 --> 00:08:00.072
Change of plans.

153
00:08:00.146 --> 00:08:03.582
Frankie Santoro's kid may
have been hit last night.

154
00:08:03.649 --> 00:08:04.741
I've got to see for myself.

155
00:08:04.817 --> 00:08:06.717
What about...

156
00:08:06.786 --> 00:08:08.583
She's coming with.

157
00:08:08.654 --> 00:08:09.643
Fun.

158
00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:14.884
Hi. Stan.

159
00:08:14.961 --> 00:08:16.053
<i>Marshall...</i>

160
00:08:16.128 --> 00:08:19.393
What? I'm sorry. Stan.
You're breaking up.

161
00:08:22.101 --> 00:08:24.899
<i>Frankie Santoro.
aka Frankie Nuts.</i>

162
00:08:24.971 --> 00:08:27.337
<i>a nickname not bestowed
for his love of filberts.</i>

163
00:08:27.406 --> 00:08:30.341
<i>earned his ticket into witness
protection by agreeing to testify</i>

164
00:08:30.409 --> 00:08:32.707
<i>against his former boss.
Dominick Mastro.</i>

165
00:08:32.778 --> 00:08:34.803
<i>last of the big-time Dons.</i>

166
00:08:34.881 --> 00:08:37.247
<i>Frankie had the misfortune
of whacking Petey Lorusso</i>

167
00:08:37.316 --> 00:08:39.045
<i>while he was under
FBI surveillance.</i>

168
00:08:39.118 --> 00:08:43.350
<i>which coincidentally was
also Petey's misfortune.</i>

169
00:08:51.097 --> 00:08:53.531
Wow. Just like
the motion pictures.

170
00:08:55.101 --> 00:08:57.092
Can I get you something?
A bromo?

171
00:08:57.169 --> 00:08:59.501
Tasha. just stay in the car.
This will just take a few minutes.

172
00:08:59.572 --> 00:09:00.561
Okay.

173
00:09:03.442 --> 00:09:05.842
Please don't let this
be Frankie's kid.

174
00:09:05.912 --> 00:09:08.244
Should I call Jinx now and
tell her to cancel your party?

175
00:09:08.314 --> 00:09:12.512
If you were any kind of friend. you
would have done that a long time ago.

176
00:09:14.787 --> 00:09:15.845
You the lead on this?

177
00:09:15.922 --> 00:09:17.947
Yeah. unfortunately.

178
00:09:18.024 --> 00:09:19.855
Detective Dershowitz.

179
00:09:19.926 --> 00:09:21.393
Dershowitz? Really?

180
00:09:21.460 --> 00:09:22.859
Yeah. long story.

181
00:09:22.929 --> 00:09:24.191
I'll bet.

182
00:09:24.263 --> 00:09:26.629
Everyone calls me Bobby.
Or Bobby D.

183
00:09:26.699 --> 00:09:28.894
Mary Shannon.
U.S. Marshals.

184
00:09:28.968 --> 00:09:30.265
So. why did you call
the Marshals. Detective?

185
00:09:30.336 --> 00:09:33.464
Well. we got two dead kids. We have
a girl named Sienna Burke. over there.

186
00:09:33.539 --> 00:09:35.939
And a boy with
this in his wallet.

187
00:09:38.110 --> 00:09:39.668
And this.

188
00:09:40.813 --> 00:09:42.440
It was tucked
behind the other one.

189
00:09:42.515 --> 00:09:46.178
Kid with two identities. It occurred
to me he might be in Witness Protection.

190
00:09:46.252 --> 00:09:47.844
You got all that
from a fake ID?

191
00:09:47.920 --> 00:09:50.354
Yeah. I'm intuitive
that way.

192
00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:52.279
All right. thanks.

193
00:09:52.358 --> 00:09:53.723
Uh... that's evidence.

194
00:09:53.793 --> 00:09:57.354
Uh-huh. So. any thoughts
about what happened?

195
00:09:57.430 --> 00:10:00.126
And you're asking me.
what. out of professional curiosity?

196
00:10:00.199 --> 00:10:02.895
Sure. let's go with that.

197
00:10:02.969 --> 00:10:04.994
Well. the girl's
father is Cale Burke.

198
00:10:05.071 --> 00:10:06.163
He's the developer
of this land.

199
00:10:06.238 --> 00:10:09.105
a project that's been contested in
and out of court for about a decade.

200
00:10:09.175 --> 00:10:10.199
By whom?

201
00:10:10.276 --> 00:10:13.507
You name it. Local Indians.
business groups. zero growth nuts.

202
00:10:13.579 --> 00:10:15.945
And you think somebody unhappy about
the project might have done this?

203
00:10:16.015 --> 00:10:18.984
Aw. Hell if I know. But
it's a place to start. right?

204
00:10:19.051 --> 00:10:21.679
Unless. of course. you think I
should be looking someplace else.

205
00:10:21.754 --> 00:10:24.552
Nope. Sounds to me like you're
heading in the right direction.

206
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:26.251
Yeah. that's what I thought.

207
00:10:26.325 --> 00:10:28.088
Thanks for the call.
Mmm-hmm.

208
00:10:30.563 --> 00:10:32.326
Hey.

209
00:10:32.398 --> 00:10:33.990
What's with the
silent sentinels?

210
00:10:34.066 --> 00:10:35.090
Huh?

211
00:10:35.167 --> 00:10:36.429
The guys on the bikes.

212
00:10:36.502 --> 00:10:38.299
Oh. they've been
watching all morning.

213
00:10:38.371 --> 00:10:39.770
They make
all these tracks?

214
00:10:39.839 --> 00:10:41.329
Yeah. probably.

215
00:10:41.407 --> 00:10:43.238
And you're not
questioning them because...

216
00:10:43.309 --> 00:10:45.573
Well. because chasing
Indians on dirt bikes

217
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:48.978
through the desert seems
like a poor use of my talent.

218
00:10:49.048 --> 00:10:50.174
Makes sense.

219
00:10:50.249 --> 00:10:52.444
Hey. How about it?
He one of yours?

220
00:10:54.086 --> 00:10:56.452
Afraid I don't know
what you're talking about.

221
00:10:56.522 --> 00:10:58.456
But thanks again
for the call.

222
00:10:58.524 --> 00:11:00.048
That's right. You're the
branch of law enforcement

223
00:11:00.126 --> 00:11:02.856
that puts criminals
back on the street. right?

224
00:11:09.602 --> 00:11:12.230
It's Santoro's kid.

225
00:11:12.304 --> 00:11:14.465
For sure?

226
00:11:14.540 --> 00:11:17.065
If this is who's
lying under that sheet.

227
00:11:29.689 --> 00:11:31.179
Oh. God.

228
00:11:34.393 --> 00:11:36.258
What a waste.

229
00:11:39.098 --> 00:11:41.862
Hey. Don't touch that.

230
00:11:41.934 --> 00:11:43.492
Can't you shut his eyes?

231
00:11:43.569 --> 00:11:46.163
Only if you got a
needle and thread.

232
00:11:56.582 --> 00:11:59.710
Any thoughts on why he gets it in the back
of the head. and she gets hers in the face?

233
00:11:59.785 --> 00:12:03.346
She was running. Took two in
the spine. taking out her legs.

234
00:12:03.422 --> 00:12:04.650
Then. they turned her over.

235
00:12:04.724 --> 00:12:06.589
And finished her
off in the face?

236
00:12:06.659 --> 00:12:08.183
Not quite.

237
00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.553
Good God.

238
00:12:11.630 --> 00:12:13.097
Somebody was pissed off.

239
00:12:13.165 --> 00:12:15.827
This goes way
beyond pissed off.

240
00:12:15.901 --> 00:12:18.028
She was alive
for most of this.

241
00:12:26.078 --> 00:12:28.603
So. you think this was a message
to Frankie Senior?

242
00:12:28.681 --> 00:12:31.912
I don't know. That kind of violence.
you've got to believe she was the target.

243
00:12:31.984 --> 00:12:35.977
Plus. if they find Junior. they found
Senior. So. why not just take Frankie out?

244
00:12:36.055 --> 00:12:37.613
Why not just
take Frankie out?

245
00:12:37.690 --> 00:12:39.317
Unless they don't
want him dead.

246
00:12:39.391 --> 00:12:41.325
Maybe they just want him
to queer his testimony.

247
00:12:41.393 --> 00:12:46.327
That could hurt a case
worse than him not showing up.

248
00:12:46.398 --> 00:12:48.366
Please stop that.

249
00:12:48.434 --> 00:12:49.833
Then again. anyone
who knows Frankie

250
00:12:49.902 --> 00:12:51.699
knows killing his kid is
not the way to motivate him.

251
00:12:51.771 --> 00:12:53.739
So. you think he's not
going to be happy about this?

252
00:12:53.806 --> 00:12:56.070
Have you noticed I'm
not in a joking mood?

253
00:12:56.142 --> 00:12:57.234
Sorry.

254
00:12:57.309 --> 00:13:00.176
I've got to go find Frankie.

255
00:13:00.246 --> 00:13:02.806
Tasha. I told you
to wait in the car.

256
00:13:04.383 --> 00:13:05.975
It was so hot in there.

257
00:13:06.051 --> 00:13:09.077
Okay. It's okay. Come on.
Let's get you home.

258
00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:22.092
Aw. That makes me sad.

259
00:13:32.111 --> 00:13:34.011
Why are we stopping here?

260
00:13:34.079 --> 00:13:35.979
Just stay in the car.
and don't touch anything.

261
00:13:36.048 --> 00:13:37.913
No. Hey! Wait! No.

262
00:13:39.151 --> 00:13:40.277
<i>Hey. amigo. Qué pasa?</i>

263
00:13:40.352 --> 00:13:41.478
<i>Yo. G.
Todo bien?</i>

264
00:13:41.554 --> 00:13:42.612
What's up?

265
00:13:42.688 --> 00:13:44.178
Just keep an eye
on the ride for me.

266
00:13:44.256 --> 00:13:47.054
Make sure nothing bad
happens to the car or to her.

267
00:13:49.628 --> 00:13:50.856
Mostly. to the car.

268
00:13:50.930 --> 00:13:52.659
All right.

269
00:13:53.799 --> 00:13:56.427
<i>Hey. mami!
What's cracking?</i>

270
00:13:56.502 --> 00:13:58.936
You want to "F" off?

271
00:14:02.208 --> 00:14:05.006
Here you go. Padre. Twenty
tickets for Wednesday night.

272
00:14:07.479 --> 00:14:08.741
Bleachers.

273
00:14:12.551 --> 00:14:14.143
So. did you take
her to my house?

274
00:14:14.220 --> 00:14:15.517
Not exactly.

275
00:14:15.588 --> 00:14:16.646
Raph. what did you do?

276
00:14:16.722 --> 00:14:20.021
I left her sitting in my car
in front of the youth center

277
00:14:20.092 --> 00:14:23.391
with a couple of junior
cholos scoping her out.

278
00:14:23.462 --> 00:14:24.622
<i>She's totally freaking out.</i>

279
00:14:24.697 --> 00:14:25.823
You did that?

280
00:14:25.898 --> 00:14:27.661
Yeah. Pretty funny. huh?

281
00:14:27.733 --> 00:14:29.928
Oh. yeah. But not
the way you think.

282
00:14:30.002 --> 00:14:31.469
What's that mean?

283
00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:35.064
It means my sister has a
penchant for boosting cars.

284
00:14:35.140 --> 00:14:36.198
A penchant?

285
00:14:36.275 --> 00:14:37.674
More like a compulsion.

286
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:46.245
Son of a bitch.

287
00:14:46.318 --> 00:14:48.047
I thought I told you
to watch the car.

288
00:14:48.120 --> 00:14:49.109
<i>We did. ese.</i>

289
00:14:49.188 --> 00:14:51.213
Yeah. G. There it go.

290
00:14:52.625 --> 00:14:55.219
Mary. You better
come pick me up.

291
00:14:55.294 --> 00:14:58.889
Ah. I'm sorry. I can't hear you.
You're breaking up.

292
00:15:01.467 --> 00:15:02.729
Brandi.

293
00:15:04.203 --> 00:15:06.034
Oh. Lord.

294
00:15:33.999 --> 00:15:35.489
Just a second.

295
00:15:47.947 --> 00:15:49.505
Okay.

296
00:15:52.851 --> 00:15:55.183
Phone works.

297
00:15:55.254 --> 00:15:59.020
No. No. no. no.
I wish to go home.

298
00:15:59.091 --> 00:16:01.218
This is your home. now.

299
00:16:01.293 --> 00:16:03.887
No! No! No!

300
00:16:06.165 --> 00:16:09.726
Please. It's not possible!

301
00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:12.270
Tasha. Tasha. Tasha!
Listen to me.

302
00:16:12.338 --> 00:16:14.670
You can't go back.
You can never go back.

303
00:16:14.740 --> 00:16:15.832
You know what
they'll do to you.

304
00:16:15.908 --> 00:16:18.308
I am just bookkeeper!

305
00:16:18.377 --> 00:16:19.605
I know.

306
00:16:21.113 --> 00:16:22.410
I know. I know.

307
00:16:23.749 --> 00:16:26.047
Let it out.

308
00:16:26.118 --> 00:16:29.645
Okay. Okay.
It's okay. Let it out.

309
00:16:32.491 --> 00:16:34.459
How this can happen?

310
00:16:34.526 --> 00:16:37.927
My life. My... family.

311
00:16:39.765 --> 00:16:41.892
Everything gone.

312
00:16:44.069 --> 00:16:48.369
They don't even let
me bring pictures.

313
00:16:48.440 --> 00:16:52.171
I know. It isn't fair.
But listen to me.

314
00:16:52.244 --> 00:16:55.907
You did a great. courageous
thing. testifying. Okay?

315
00:16:55.981 --> 00:16:58.973
And now. it's time
to focus on the future.

316
00:16:59.051 --> 00:17:01.679
Think of it as a chance
to build a whole new life.

317
00:17:01.754 --> 00:17:03.813
Even better than
the one you had before.

318
00:17:06.458 --> 00:17:08.187
But you cannot.

319
00:17:08.260 --> 00:17:11.821
under any circumstances. no matter
how homesick or lonely you get.

320
00:17:11.897 --> 00:17:13.660
go back home.

321
00:17:13.732 --> 00:17:16.667
Or contact anyone
from your past.

322
00:17:16.735 --> 00:17:18.168
Do you understand?

323
00:17:21.106 --> 00:17:22.937
Do you understand?

324
00:17:24.610 --> 00:17:29.638
No one in your new life can ever
know your old identity. Okay?

325
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:31.740
Boyfriends.
coworkers. no one.

326
00:17:31.817 --> 00:17:33.216
And if you...

327
00:17:33.285 --> 00:17:37.949
If you think for a minute that someone
recognizes you. you have to call me immediately.

328
00:17:38.023 --> 00:17:39.354
Is all this clear?

329
00:17:41.126 --> 00:17:45.290
That girl... on ground.
She was witness?

330
00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:48.365
No.

331
00:17:48.434 --> 00:17:50.163
No. No.

332
00:17:51.370 --> 00:17:53.736
She had nothing to do
with witness protection.

333
00:17:55.607 --> 00:17:58.269
Sweetie. trust me.

334
00:17:59.611 --> 00:18:01.875
You're going to be okay.

335
00:18:01.947 --> 00:18:03.574
In the history of the
Witness Protection Program.

336
00:18:03.649 --> 00:18:06.447
no one who's followed the
rules has ever been harmed.

337
00:18:08.287 --> 00:18:11.814
As long as you do as I say.
nothing bad will happen to you.

338
00:18:15.094 --> 00:18:18.461
You can do this.
Okay? I know you can.

339
00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:25.060
Come on. Come on. Stand up.

340
00:18:26.839 --> 00:18:30.468
How about you rest for a
little while. watch some T.V.

341
00:18:30.542 --> 00:18:32.840
Cable's not hooked up. yet.

342
00:18:32.911 --> 00:18:36.506
Yeah. all right. I'll. um...
I'll get the cable turned on.

343
00:18:36.582 --> 00:18:39.278
And a little later. I'll
come by with some groceries.

344
00:18:41.787 --> 00:18:43.812
Is there anything
special you need?

345
00:18:45.624 --> 00:18:47.023
It's okay.

346
00:18:48.327 --> 00:18:50.056
Take your time.

347
00:18:53.031 --> 00:18:54.430
Uh...

348
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.968
They promise me new breasts.

349
00:18:59.538 --> 00:19:01.369
When I can get them?

350
00:19:04.676 --> 00:19:06.837
No. Between one and five
isn't good enough. Federico.

351
00:19:06.912 --> 00:19:08.675
Our friend needs
her cable on now.

352
00:19:08.747 --> 00:19:11.307
So. get it done or we're
switching to satellite.

353
00:19:11.383 --> 00:19:12.680
You think that's funny?

354
00:19:12.751 --> 00:19:16.847
How about we switch to satellite.
then I punch you in the face?

355
00:19:16.922 --> 00:19:19.618
She's home now. I'll tell
her you're on your way.

356
00:19:19.691 --> 00:19:21.659
So. anyway. If you could
start processing info.

357
00:19:21.727 --> 00:19:23.388
Little Frankie.
the girl. her father.

358
00:19:23.462 --> 00:19:25.657
Friends and family of everyone
Frankie's testifying against.

359
00:19:25.731 --> 00:19:27.665
Whatever else
you can think of.

360
00:19:33.438 --> 00:19:34.530
Please.

361
00:19:34.606 --> 00:19:37.575
You know. I'm not
your assistant.

362
00:19:37.643 --> 00:19:40.373
I have a couple dozen witnesses
of my own to deal with.

363
00:19:40.445 --> 00:19:43.937
Oh. yeah? Any of their kids
get murdered last night?

364
00:19:44.016 --> 00:19:45.540
I'll have to check.

365
00:19:47.152 --> 00:19:48.642
Oh. fine.
Thank you.

366
00:19:50.289 --> 00:19:51.620
Pissy little girl.

367
00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:53.214
I heard that!

368
00:19:58.797 --> 00:20:00.788
I don't give a rat's ass
about your protocol.

369
00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:02.993
I've got two parents on their
way down here to see their son.

370
00:20:03.068 --> 00:20:05.400
And trust me on this one. This is
not where you want them to find him.

371
00:20:05.470 --> 00:20:08.098
Then you better keep them out of
here. because a van full of illegals

372
00:20:08.173 --> 00:20:09.936
plowed into a bridge
abutment this morning.

373
00:20:10.008 --> 00:20:12.238
And I'm under-staffed. I won't
know which one of these is yours

374
00:20:12.311 --> 00:20:13.573
until I start
processing them.

375
00:20:13.645 --> 00:20:14.907
Yeah? Well. how long
is that going to take?

376
00:20:14.980 --> 00:20:16.572
As long as it takes.

377
00:20:16.648 --> 00:20:18.912
Look. Well. work quickly.

378
00:20:18.984 --> 00:20:20.042
Frankie.

379
00:20:20.118 --> 00:20:22.052
Where is he? Come on.
Come on back inside.

380
00:20:22.120 --> 00:20:23.144
Is one of these Frankie?

381
00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:24.382
Please. just come
back inside.

382
00:20:24.456 --> 00:20:25.980
Is my boy in
one of these bags?

383
00:20:26.058 --> 00:20:27.116
Frankie.

384
00:20:27.192 --> 00:20:29.752
Hey. Excuse me. Sir. you cannot... Hey!

385
00:20:29.828 --> 00:20:32.991
Hey! Frankie! Frankie!

386
00:20:34.032 --> 00:20:35.260
Oh. my God.

387
00:20:35.334 --> 00:20:38.303
Where's my boy?
Where's my boy?

388
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:42.833
Frankie. stop it.
Frankie. Frankie.

389
00:20:42.908 --> 00:20:44.933
Frankie stop it!
Stop it!

390
00:20:45.010 --> 00:20:48.741
Get off me! Do not
put your hands on me!

391
00:21:09.768 --> 00:21:13.727
Felicia. Felicia.
Oh. my God.

392
00:21:13.805 --> 00:21:14.931
Felicia.

393
00:21:16.341 --> 00:21:19.606
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

394
00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:30.886
Frankie. wait.

395
00:21:30.956 --> 00:21:32.446
Frankie?

396
00:21:34.259 --> 00:21:36.227
Frankie? Frankie!

397
00:21:37.529 --> 00:21:38.791
Frankie. wait!

398
00:21:38.864 --> 00:21:39.922
What? What do you want?

399
00:21:39.998 --> 00:21:42.364
Don't "what" me. I know you.
I know what you're thinking.

400
00:21:42.434 --> 00:21:44.925
Oh. congratulations. You're
the Amazing freaking Kreskin.

401
00:21:45.003 --> 00:21:46.527
I have no idea who that
is. But listen to me.

402
00:21:46.605 --> 00:21:47.970
If you go off gunning
for whoever did this.

403
00:21:48.040 --> 00:21:50.031
you're going to blow
your whole plea agreement.

404
00:21:50.108 --> 00:21:51.803
Did you just see
my boy in there?

405
00:21:51.877 --> 00:21:55.005
I know. Frankie.
I know. I'm so sorry.

406
00:21:55.847 --> 00:21:58.008
But Felicia needs
you now. Okay?

407
00:21:58.083 --> 00:22:00.950
Please. Please.
go take care of her.

408
00:22:01.019 --> 00:22:03.886
I swear to you.
You'll get your justice.

409
00:22:05.190 --> 00:22:07.090
You got 24 hours.

410
00:22:07.159 --> 00:22:10.959
After that. I take matters into my
own hands and to hell with this plea.

411
00:22:11.029 --> 00:22:13.088
Frankie.
As far as justice.

412
00:22:13.165 --> 00:22:15.759
you got your version.
I got mine.

413
00:22:37.989 --> 00:22:39.081
What are you doing here?

414
00:22:39.157 --> 00:22:40.385
I work here. Stan.

415
00:22:40.459 --> 00:22:42.290
Why aren't you helping
Mary move Frankie Nuts?

416
00:22:42.361 --> 00:22:43.692
She wanted me here
doing this.

417
00:22:43.762 --> 00:22:46.754
And you thought it was okay to let her
handle that sick bastard by herself?

418
00:22:46.832 --> 00:22:50.529
Her witness. Her call.
It how we do. G.

419
00:22:51.970 --> 00:22:53.335
If anything
happens to her...

420
00:22:53.405 --> 00:22:54.872
Relax.

421
00:22:54.940 --> 00:22:56.931
Mary knows
what she's doing.

422
00:23:00.345 --> 00:23:01.778
So. did you get her
a birthday present?

423
00:23:01.847 --> 00:23:04.179
I'm working her case.
You don't think that's enough?

424
00:23:04.249 --> 00:23:05.716
Even you're not that dumb.

425
00:23:05.784 --> 00:23:09.345
I'm smart enough to know
you can't shop for Mary.

426
00:23:10.956 --> 00:23:12.514
What about you?

427
00:23:12.591 --> 00:23:16.152
Oh. Well. I just
got her a. uh...

428
00:23:16.228 --> 00:23:18.822
Bottle of really
expensive perfume.

429
00:23:18.897 --> 00:23:20.728
Mary doesn't wear perfume.

430
00:23:20.799 --> 00:23:21.823
Yes. she does.

431
00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:22.924
Uh-uh.

432
00:23:23.001 --> 00:23:24.935
You sure? I mean.
she always smells so good.

433
00:23:25.003 --> 00:23:26.630
That's just her.

434
00:23:30.342 --> 00:23:31.866
Huh.

435
00:23:50.462 --> 00:23:52.953
I can't believe you're
putting us in this place.

436
00:23:53.031 --> 00:23:54.658
I'm sorry.
I wish it were nicer.

437
00:23:54.733 --> 00:23:57.964
but discretionary spending
isn't what it used to be.

438
00:23:58.036 --> 00:24:00.732
Why can't we go home?

439
00:24:00.806 --> 00:24:05.300
I need to go home
to plan Frankie's funeral.

440
00:24:05.377 --> 00:24:09.211
I promise I'll get you home
as soon as I can. Okay?

441
00:24:09.281 --> 00:24:12.682
Whoever did this to little
Frankie is still out there.

442
00:24:12.751 --> 00:24:15.914
Until we know otherwise. I have
to assume he's coming for you next.

443
00:24:15.987 --> 00:24:17.454
Let him come.

444
00:24:19.391 --> 00:24:21.484
This is on you. Frank.

445
00:24:37.776 --> 00:24:39.710
I've got to
ask you. Frankie.

446
00:24:39.778 --> 00:24:40.938
Do you know
anything about this?

447
00:24:41.012 --> 00:24:42.206
No.

448
00:24:42.280 --> 00:24:44.145
Of course. you would
never lie to me.

449
00:24:45.717 --> 00:24:46.945
All right. then.

450
00:24:47.018 --> 00:24:49.509
Stay in the room with your
wife and let me do my job.

451
00:24:49.588 --> 00:24:51.783
Well. you've got
about 23 hours.

452
00:24:51.857 --> 00:24:54.849
And then. I assure you.
I will do my job.

453
00:25:07.005 --> 00:25:09.769
<i>The care and feeding of career
criminals like Frankie Nuts</i>

454
00:25:09.841 --> 00:25:12.935
<i>is a dicey proposition at
best. more art than science.</i>

455
00:25:13.011 --> 00:25:15.309
<i>requiring a closet
full of hats.</i>

456
00:25:15.380 --> 00:25:18.747
<i>On any given day. I get to play
mother. father. best friend.</i>

457
00:25:18.817 --> 00:25:23.277
<i>priest. rabbi. marriage counselor.
employment agent. bodyguard.</i>

458
00:25:23.355 --> 00:25:26.984
<i>And. yes. unfortunately.
occasionally homicide detective.</i>

459
00:25:27.058 --> 00:25:29.754
<i>Which is why I find myself
driving my misogynist metaphor</i>

460
00:25:29.828 --> 00:25:32.991
<i>across the desert in the 110 degree
heat with a busted air conditioner</i>

461
00:25:33.064 --> 00:25:36.295
<i>to hunt down the murderer of
the son of my murderer witness.</i>

462
00:25:36.368 --> 00:25:40.862
<i>No back-up. No plan to
speak of. No alternative.</i>

463
00:25:40.939 --> 00:25:45.137
<i>Also. Frankie Junior got killed on
my watch. That just pisses me off.</i>

464
00:25:57.522 --> 00:25:58.989
Nice chaps.

465
00:26:02.527 --> 00:26:04.051
Aw.

466
00:26:06.998 --> 00:26:11.594
Oh. come on. fellows. What do you say
we turn those frowns upside down. huh?

467
00:26:13.471 --> 00:26:15.871
Write down your
customers' names.

468
00:26:17.676 --> 00:26:20.076
I've never seen
these people before.

469
00:26:20.712 --> 00:26:22.805
Listen.

470
00:26:22.881 --> 00:26:25.645
Here's the deal. Two kids were
killed about a mile from here.

471
00:26:25.717 --> 00:26:28.618
And at least a few of these
guys were at the murder site.

472
00:26:28.687 --> 00:26:29.881
So. please.

473
00:26:29.955 --> 00:26:32.219
Save us both a lot of trouble
and just write the damn names

474
00:26:32.290 --> 00:26:36.852
before Great White Father back in Washington
goes all Little Bighorn on your ass.

475
00:26:36.928 --> 00:26:39.624
You're kidding me. right?

476
00:26:39.698 --> 00:26:42.963
Was that over
the top? Too much?

477
00:26:43.034 --> 00:26:45.025
I kind of suck at that
whole bad cop thing.

478
00:26:45.103 --> 00:26:46.798
Look. First of all.

479
00:26:46.871 --> 00:26:49.806
it was you guys that got your
asses kicked at Little Bighorn.

480
00:26:49.874 --> 00:26:50.898
Really?

481
00:26:50.976 --> 00:26:54.844
And second of all. today's
my first day of work here.

482
00:26:54.913 --> 00:26:57.404
And I have really never
seen these people before.

483
00:26:57.482 --> 00:27:00.076
Sorry. I thought you
were being difficult.

484
00:27:09.327 --> 00:27:10.658
Excuse me.

485
00:27:15.867 --> 00:27:18.358
Good lord.

486
00:27:18.436 --> 00:27:19.926
What is it with
men's restrooms?

487
00:27:20.005 --> 00:27:23.065
Do you all like the smell of
stale urine? Is that what it is?

488
00:27:23.141 --> 00:27:27.009
Okay. Enough chit-chat. What's your
name and did you kill those two kids?

489
00:27:28.747 --> 00:27:31.614
I'm sorry. Are you
talking to me?

490
00:27:33.151 --> 00:27:34.140
Aw.

491
00:27:34.219 --> 00:27:35.243
What's so funny?

492
00:27:35.320 --> 00:27:36.878
It's so cute.

493
00:27:36.955 --> 00:27:39.719
Well. it's like one of those mini
taquitos they serve at happy hour.

494
00:27:39.791 --> 00:27:41.315
Oh. yeah?
You want some?

495
00:27:41.393 --> 00:27:42.655
Ew.

496
00:27:44.462 --> 00:27:46.828
Manly. yes.
But I like it. too.

497
00:27:46.898 --> 00:27:49.366
Now. what do you say you answer my
questions before I drag you out of here

498
00:27:49.434 --> 00:27:51.265
by your surprisingly
small wee-wee?

499
00:27:51.336 --> 00:27:55.534
Okay. Okay.
My name is George Parker.

500
00:27:55.607 --> 00:27:57.575
And no. I didn't
kill those two kids.

501
00:27:57.642 --> 00:27:59.667
So. what were you doing there
this morning. George?

502
00:27:59.744 --> 00:28:04.010
The usual. Pulling up surveyor's
stakes. hassling workers.

503
00:28:04.082 --> 00:28:08.678
And then. one of the guys. they found
the dead bodies. We hung around to watch.

504
00:28:08.753 --> 00:28:10.448
What's your beef
with the project?

505
00:28:10.522 --> 00:28:13.286
Same old story.
Eminent domain.

506
00:28:13.358 --> 00:28:14.518
Come again?

507
00:28:14.592 --> 00:28:18.528
Indians getting their land ripped
off for commercial development.

508
00:28:18.596 --> 00:28:22.157
Huh. So. killing the developer's
daughter sounds like pretty good payback.

509
00:28:22.233 --> 00:28:25.862
Maybe. Except the developer isn't the
one that screwed us out of the land.

510
00:28:25.937 --> 00:28:27.063
Huh?

511
00:28:28.773 --> 00:28:31.401
Talk to a dude named
Edwin Talltrees.

512
00:28:31.476 --> 00:28:32.943
He's the guy that
ripped us off.

513
00:28:33.011 --> 00:28:34.603
An Indian?

514
00:28:34.679 --> 00:28:35.737
That's right.

515
00:28:35.814 --> 00:28:37.907
Why would he kill
two kids on his own land?

516
00:28:37.982 --> 00:28:39.882
Because it isn't
his land anymore.

517
00:28:39.951 --> 00:28:43.648
After he screwed us. the dead
girl's father screwed him.

518
00:28:43.722 --> 00:28:45.656
Sounds like a lot of
screwing going on.

519
00:28:45.724 --> 00:28:47.385
Uh-huh.

520
00:28:47.459 --> 00:28:50.758
All right. then. George.
You can zip it up.

521
00:28:50.829 --> 00:28:52.820
Sorry about the
small wee-wee crack.

522
00:28:52.897 --> 00:28:54.888
It's been a bitch of a day.

523
00:28:59.504 --> 00:29:02.405
That is one special guy.

524
00:29:02.474 --> 00:29:04.374
God. I hope he calls.

525
00:29:42.881 --> 00:29:46.078
Apparently. ripping off your
own people has its upside.

526
00:29:48.553 --> 00:29:50.953
I wish I had
people to rip off.

527
00:29:58.196 --> 00:29:59.891
Can I help you?

528
00:29:59.964 --> 00:30:01.761
Hi.

529
00:30:01.833 --> 00:30:05.325
Mary Shannon with the U.S.
Marshals. You Edwin Talltrees?

530
00:30:05.403 --> 00:30:07.735
I am. Come on down.

531
00:30:07.806 --> 00:30:09.296
All right.

532
00:30:11.442 --> 00:30:14.502
Must be a bitch getting
pizza delivered up here.

533
00:30:22.453 --> 00:30:23.545
Hi.

534
00:30:24.956 --> 00:30:26.719
Have a seat.
Thanks.

535
00:30:28.593 --> 00:30:31.960
I suppose you're here about
Sienna Burke and that boy.

536
00:30:32.030 --> 00:30:33.827
Why would you suppose that?

537
00:30:33.898 --> 00:30:38.130
It's no secret Cale Burke and I had a
dispute about that specific piece of land.

538
00:30:38.203 --> 00:30:40.831
You'd be remiss
not to question me.

539
00:30:40.905 --> 00:30:43.669
God knows
I hate being remiss.

540
00:30:43.741 --> 00:30:47.040
So. what can you tell me
about the murders?

541
00:30:47.111 --> 00:30:48.703
I'm curious.

542
00:30:50.882 --> 00:30:54.340
Why is the U.S. Marshals Service
interested in a local murder?

543
00:30:58.556 --> 00:30:59.648
Hey.

544
00:31:01.125 --> 00:31:02.752
Here's an idea.

545
00:31:02.827 --> 00:31:05.261
Since I'm the one
wearing the badge

546
00:31:05.330 --> 00:31:07.525
and you're the
murder suspect.

547
00:31:07.599 --> 00:31:10.261
how about we stick to
me asking the questions?

548
00:31:11.669 --> 00:31:12.931
All right.

549
00:31:14.706 --> 00:31:17.140
Cale Burke and I
attended Stanford together.

550
00:31:17.208 --> 00:31:18.869
I stood up for him
at his wedding.

551
00:31:18.943 --> 00:31:21.810
I was at the hospital
the day Sienna was born.

552
00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:26.180
She and my son. Kyle.
played together every day

553
00:31:26.251 --> 00:31:28.344
until they went off to
different private schools.

554
00:31:28.419 --> 00:31:32.913
I would give anything.
everything to bring her back.

555
00:31:36.127 --> 00:31:38.459
What else?

556
00:31:38.529 --> 00:31:40.326
Where were you last night?

557
00:31:40.398 --> 00:31:42.730
Here. With Kyle.

558
00:31:42.800 --> 00:31:45.598
Watching the Karate
Championships on Pay-Per-View.

559
00:31:45.670 --> 00:31:48.036
We're both students
of tae kwan do.

560
00:31:48.106 --> 00:31:51.542
You get much call for
that in real estate?

561
00:31:51.609 --> 00:31:53.304
Is there anything
else. Marshal?

562
00:31:54.345 --> 00:31:56.040
Is Kyle available?

563
00:31:56.114 --> 00:31:59.174
I'd rather you didn't speak to
Kyle. He's very upset about Sienna.

564
00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:01.878
Would you rather I take
him in for questioning?

565
00:32:07.759 --> 00:32:09.556
<i>Kyle?
Yeah?</i>

566
00:32:09.627 --> 00:32:11.390
Come down here. please.

567
00:32:11.462 --> 00:32:12.759
<i>Just a minute.</i>

568
00:32:14.599 --> 00:32:15.657
Now. please.

569
00:32:15.733 --> 00:32:16.859
<i>Okay.</i>

570
00:32:26.611 --> 00:32:27.805
Yummy.

571
00:32:37.689 --> 00:32:38.986
Kyle.

572
00:32:39.724 --> 00:32:41.021
What is it?

573
00:32:41.092 --> 00:32:43.993
This is Marshal Shannon. She
wants to ask you about Sienna.

574
00:32:45.563 --> 00:32:46.621
Okay.

575
00:32:46.698 --> 00:32:48.461
I understand you
were good friends.

576
00:32:48.533 --> 00:32:49.830
Were.

577
00:32:50.735 --> 00:32:53.795
Since Dad and Uncle Cale
had their disagreement

578
00:32:53.871 --> 00:32:56.396
we weren't allowed to
see each other anymore.

579
00:32:56.474 --> 00:32:58.066
Did you know the
boy she was with?

580
00:32:58.142 --> 00:32:59.734
Uh-uh.

581
00:32:59.811 --> 00:33:01.836
I just heard he
went to her school.

582
00:33:01.913 --> 00:33:05.713
Can you think of anyone who
would want to do this to Sienna?

583
00:33:05.783 --> 00:33:07.842
Everybody loved her.

584
00:33:07.919 --> 00:33:09.443
She was like...

585
00:33:11.422 --> 00:33:14.186
Well. you just couldn't
help it. you know?

586
00:33:14.258 --> 00:33:15.782
Is that enough?

587
00:33:16.728 --> 00:33:17.854
Sure.

588
00:33:17.929 --> 00:33:19.726
Just one more thing.

589
00:33:19.797 --> 00:33:22.027
Where were you last night?

590
00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:25.365
I was here with my dad.
watching the Karate Championship.

591
00:33:25.436 --> 00:33:27.301
That's what I thought.

592
00:33:28.506 --> 00:33:29.734
By the way. who won?

593
00:33:29.807 --> 00:33:31.604
Edgar Sanchez.
Edgar Sanchez.

594
00:33:34.379 --> 00:33:36.973
I'm really sorry
about your friend.

595
00:33:37.048 --> 00:33:38.447
Yeah. it sucks.

596
00:33:38.516 --> 00:33:39.847
Thanks.

597
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:48.220
<i>I really wanted to turn around and
pop off one of those Columbo questions.</i>

598
00:33:48.292 --> 00:33:50.920
<i>You know. the innocuous afterthought
that lets the killer know</i>

599
00:33:50.995 --> 00:33:52.223
<i>that I know he did it.</i>

600
00:33:52.296 --> 00:33:56.062
<i>"Excuse me. Do you always wear
white shoes after Labor Day?"</i>

601
00:33:56.134 --> 00:33:59.501
<i>Unfortunately. I had no idea if Talltrees
had anything to do with the murders.</i>

602
00:33:59.570 --> 00:34:03.336
<i>And more importantly.
he wasn't wearing shoes.</i>

603
00:34:06.310 --> 00:34:08.835
<i>As good as I am at sorting
out other people's lives.</i>

604
00:34:08.913 --> 00:34:11.711
<i>you'll just have to take my
word for it. I'm really good.</i>

605
00:34:11.783 --> 00:34:14.581
<i>that talent pales compared to
my genius for keeping my own life</i>

606
00:34:14.652 --> 00:34:16.711
<i>in a constant
state of turmoil.</i>

607
00:34:26.064 --> 00:34:27.793
Please
give me the keys.

608
00:34:27.865 --> 00:34:30.425
I'm not going to ask you again.
So. just please give me my keys!

609
00:34:30.501 --> 00:34:31.729
What are you going to do?
Are you going to hit me?

610
00:34:31.803 --> 00:34:33.168
No. But give
me the keys.

611
00:34:33.237 --> 00:34:34.261
Come on. Hit me.

612
00:34:34.338 --> 00:34:35.362
Enough! Enough!

613
00:34:35.440 --> 00:34:37.237
Just give me my keys.
Enough!

614
00:34:37.308 --> 00:34:39.868
I've got enough going on without
having to deal with this BS!

615
00:34:39.944 --> 00:34:42.435
Mary. thank God you're here. They've
been like this for half an hour.

616
00:34:42.513 --> 00:34:43.775
She stole my car.

617
00:34:43.848 --> 00:34:45.509
You left me sitting in
the middle of the ghetto.

618
00:34:45.583 --> 00:34:49.713
Mary. please. Would you do something before
the neighbors think we're poor white trash?

619
00:34:49.787 --> 00:34:52.449
Oh. Obviously.
not you. Raphael.

620
00:34:52.523 --> 00:34:54.491
God. my head
is just splitting.

621
00:34:54.559 --> 00:34:55.821
She's lucky I don't
call the cops.

622
00:34:55.893 --> 00:34:57.292
Raphael. she was scared.

623
00:34:57.361 --> 00:34:59.261
Go ahead. You know what?
Call the cops.

624
00:34:59.330 --> 00:35:02.094
I'll just tell them about that dime
bag I found in the center console.

625
00:35:02.166 --> 00:35:03.497
No. no. no.
That's not mine.

626
00:35:03.568 --> 00:35:04.865
A dime bag of what? Yeah.
okay. You don't get high?

627
00:35:04.936 --> 00:35:06.563
No! No! Is that what you're telling me?

628
00:35:06.637 --> 00:35:08.002
You don't get high?
No. I don't get high.

629
00:35:08.072 --> 00:35:10.597
Okay. All right. Both
of you. stop it. Stop it!

630
00:35:10.675 --> 00:35:12.506
I don't know whose dope
it is. And I don't care.

631
00:35:12.577 --> 00:35:15.774
I want it out of here. now. I'm
a U.S. Marshal. for Christ's sake.

632
00:35:15.847 --> 00:35:19.180
Ma. go inside and take some
aspirin. Brandi. give him his keys.

633
00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:20.774
You better don't think
that stuff is mine.

634
00:35:20.852 --> 00:35:21.876
What kind of stuff?

635
00:35:21.953 --> 00:35:23.853
You better don't? Oh.
God. It doesn't matter.

636
00:35:23.921 --> 00:35:26.719
No. The hell it doesn't. You're
taking her word over mine?

637
00:35:26.791 --> 00:35:27.815
I'm not taking
anybody's word.

638
00:35:27.892 --> 00:35:30.053
What part of "I don't care whose
it is" is difficult for you?

639
00:35:30.128 --> 00:35:32.653
Is this how you thank me for
taking time out on my day off

640
00:35:32.730 --> 00:35:34.061
to pick up your
psychotic sister?

641
00:35:34.132 --> 00:35:35.463
You were supposed to
drive her to my house.

642
00:35:35.533 --> 00:35:37.057
not intentionally scare
the crap out of her.

643
00:35:37.135 --> 00:35:39.126
I had to stop at
the youth center.

644
00:35:39.203 --> 00:35:41.194
The "scaring the crap out of
her" part was just a bonus.

645
00:35:41.272 --> 00:35:43.069
It was a juvenile prank
that blew up in your face.

646
00:35:43.141 --> 00:35:45.974
Oh. Then. after she steals my car.
you don't even come and pick me up.

647
00:35:46.043 --> 00:35:49.706
I was busy. Why can't anyone get it
through their heads? I have a job.

648
00:35:49.780 --> 00:35:53.113
Oh. that's right. Everybody has got to
make time in their day. but not Mary.

649
00:35:53.184 --> 00:35:55.812
Cry me a river. What did I pull you
away from? An extra set of crunches?

650
00:35:55.887 --> 00:35:56.945
Is that all you think I do?

651
00:35:57.021 --> 00:35:59.615
No. Sometimes. I think
you work on your lats.

652
00:36:00.625 --> 00:36:01.990
Have a happy birthday.
I'm out of here.

653
00:36:02.059 --> 00:36:03.458
See you.

654
00:36:04.462 --> 00:36:06.327
You happy?

655
00:36:06.397 --> 00:36:08.627
What? I already got rid of the
stuff. What's the big drama?

656
00:36:08.699 --> 00:36:11.133
Oh. my God. Brandi! When are
you going to grow up and stop

657
00:36:11.202 --> 00:36:13.329
making life miserable
for everyone around you?

658
00:36:13.404 --> 00:36:15.065
Don't you think
that's a little harsh?

659
00:36:15.139 --> 00:36:16.265
I thought you
had a headache.

660
00:36:16.340 --> 00:36:19.776
I do. And my two girls
fighting isn't helping it any.

661
00:36:19.844 --> 00:36:21.209
You were supposed
to pick me up.

662
00:36:21.279 --> 00:36:25.079
I have a job! Okay? I
made other arrangements.

663
00:36:25.149 --> 00:36:29.677
Oh. come on. You couldn't take
an hour off from serving warrants

664
00:36:29.754 --> 00:36:33.952
or drinking coffee at the courthouse
or whatever the hell it is you do

665
00:36:34.025 --> 00:36:35.788
to pick up your sister?

666
00:36:35.860 --> 00:36:37.293
Okay. Ma.

667
00:36:37.361 --> 00:36:39.989
I know you think Brandi's
your precious baby. She's not.

668
00:36:40.064 --> 00:36:42.191
She's a virus. infecting
everyone around her.

669
00:36:42.266 --> 00:36:43.290
All right. That's enough.

670
00:36:43.367 --> 00:36:45.062
And as long as you keep propping
her up and making excuses.

671
00:36:45.136 --> 00:36:46.763
that's all she's
ever going to be.

672
00:36:46.837 --> 00:36:49.806
God. Would you stop it?
This is your baby sister.

673
00:36:49.907 --> 00:36:51.568
Now she's going to cry and
you're going to tell her

674
00:36:51.642 --> 00:36:54.133
everything's okay. And somehow. this
is all going to wind up my fault.

675
00:36:54.212 --> 00:36:56.476
So. if you don't mind. I'm going to
skip the next part of the program.

676
00:36:56.547 --> 00:36:58.708
I have to get back to
whatever the hell it is I do.

677
00:37:00.117 --> 00:37:01.744
Excuse me.

678
00:37:02.920 --> 00:37:05.548
Just give me
the damn keys.

679
00:37:05.623 --> 00:37:06.749
You want them?

680
00:37:06.824 --> 00:37:08.052
Yeah.

681
00:37:13.030 --> 00:37:14.429
Go get them.

682
00:37:17.735 --> 00:37:19.498
No. Don't touch me!

683
00:37:19.570 --> 00:37:22.539
Get your hands off of me!
Put me down!

684
00:37:26.110 --> 00:37:27.600
You get out
when I get the keys.

685
00:37:27.678 --> 00:37:29.441
Up yours!

686
00:37:29.513 --> 00:37:30.946
Classy.

687
00:37:31.015 --> 00:37:33.575
Raphael? After she
gets your keys.

688
00:37:33.651 --> 00:37:36.950
would you mind picking up
Mary's birthday cake for me?

689
00:37:39.724 --> 00:37:41.589
<i>The Federal Witness
Protection Program</i>

690
00:37:41.659 --> 00:37:44.822
<i>is the most secretive organization
in all of law enforcement.</i>

691
00:37:44.895 --> 00:37:48.353
<i>We do not talk about what we do.
Not to friends. not to family.</i>

692
00:37:48.432 --> 00:37:50.093
<i>Not even to
other U.S. Marshals.</i>

693
00:37:50.167 --> 00:37:52.761
<i>Which is why my mother. my
sister. even my boyfriend.</i>

694
00:37:52.837 --> 00:37:55.135
<i>who by the way isn't
really my boyfriend.</i>

695
00:37:55.206 --> 00:37:57.902
<i>all think I'm a glorified
messenger with a gun.</i>

696
00:37:57.975 --> 00:38:00.466
<i>And why Marshall and I work on
the roof of the Sunshine Building.</i>

697
00:38:00.578 --> 00:38:02.239
<i>while the rest of the
U.S. Marshals reside</i>

698
00:38:02.313 --> 00:38:04.247
<i>in the Pete Domenici
Federal Courthouse.</i>

699
00:38:04.315 --> 00:38:07.284
<i>with their mahogany desks.
crystal chandeliers. and butlers.</i>

700
00:38:07.351 --> 00:38:10.377
<i>And yes. his name is
Marshall and he is a marshal.</i>

701
00:38:10.454 --> 00:38:12.388
<i>Sometimes. that's just
how the universe works.</i>

702
00:38:13.891 --> 00:38:14.949
Marshall.

703
00:38:15.026 --> 00:38:16.994
<i>Hey. How's it coming?
Drips and drabs.</i>

704
00:38:17.061 --> 00:38:21.020
I tracked down the girl's best
friend. She's at work at Elsa Ross.

705
00:38:21.098 --> 00:38:22.360
So. she doesn't know?

706
00:38:22.433 --> 00:38:24.162
Either that. or she's
got a great work ethic.

707
00:38:24.235 --> 00:38:26.135
All right. I'm on my way.

708
00:38:26.203 --> 00:38:27.261
Tread lightly.

709
00:38:27.338 --> 00:38:29.101
Hey. Give me
a little credit.

710
00:38:33.077 --> 00:38:35.170
Oh. God.

711
00:38:35.246 --> 00:38:37.578
I can't believe
she's dead.

712
00:38:37.682 --> 00:38:38.910
I'm so sorry.

713
00:38:38.983 --> 00:38:43.113
And I can't believe you tried
on clothes before telling me.

714
00:38:43.187 --> 00:38:45.917
Yeah. Again.
I'm really sorry.

715
00:38:47.291 --> 00:38:50.522
I thought it would
help ease into it.

716
00:38:50.594 --> 00:38:52.824
I can see now
that was a mistake.

717
00:38:52.897 --> 00:38:54.728
Who did this?

718
00:38:54.799 --> 00:38:56.164
I don't know.

719
00:38:56.233 --> 00:38:58.929
I was hoping maybe you could
help me figure that out.

720
00:38:59.470 --> 00:39:02.962
I don't know anyone
who would do anything like this.

721
00:39:03.040 --> 00:39:05.201
All my friends
are really nice.

722
00:39:05.276 --> 00:39:08.006
Okay. Okay.
You think about it.

723
00:39:09.513 --> 00:39:12.175
I mean. what about Frankie?
Did he have any enemies?

724
00:39:12.249 --> 00:39:15.218
I don't know.
He was new.

725
00:39:15.286 --> 00:39:19.655
He... He seemed really sweet.
kind of sad. Like. lost.

726
00:39:20.891 --> 00:39:23.189
How long had he and Sienna
been going out?

727
00:39:23.260 --> 00:39:27.094
They weren't going out. Sienna
was just being nice to him.

728
00:39:28.232 --> 00:39:30.928
He was a virgin.
so. she was going to...

729
00:39:33.371 --> 00:39:34.770
You know...

730
00:39:36.841 --> 00:39:38.138
That is nice.

731
00:39:38.209 --> 00:39:39.540
Sienna was like that.

732
00:39:41.112 --> 00:39:43.580
Okay. Okay. Okay.

733
00:39:44.915 --> 00:39:47.406
I know this is hard.
But please...

734
00:39:47.485 --> 00:39:49.282
Please.
Try to think. Nicole.

735
00:39:49.353 --> 00:39:50.547
Is there anyone
we should talk to?

736
00:39:50.621 --> 00:39:53.283
Anyone you'd want to talk to
if you were me?

737
00:39:53.357 --> 00:39:56.520
She had a boyfriend.
I'd want to talk to him.

738
00:39:57.528 --> 00:40:00.053
Okay. Good.
What was his name?

739
00:40:00.131 --> 00:40:05.034
I don't know. He was this big
secret. And I mean really big.

740
00:40:05.603 --> 00:40:09.403
She wouldn't even tell me what he
looked like. And she told me everything.

741
00:40:09.473 --> 00:40:12.271
Did she tell you anything
about him? Anything at all?

742
00:40:12.343 --> 00:40:16.507
Mmm-mmm. Just that he made her
get this stupid tattoo

743
00:40:16.580 --> 00:40:18.343
and she totally
didn't want to.

744
00:40:18.416 --> 00:40:20.316
You mean the one
on her chest?

745
00:40:20.384 --> 00:40:22.909
Yeah. Over her heart.

746
00:40:23.554 --> 00:40:28.389
It was supposed to be some
symbol of their everlasting love.

747
00:40:29.827 --> 00:40:32.352
So. how come she was with
Frankie? I mean. if she had this

748
00:40:32.430 --> 00:40:34.557
secret boyfriend and all?

749
00:40:34.632 --> 00:40:37.430
Because they broke up.
like. a month ago.

750
00:40:39.336 --> 00:40:41.634
Did I forget to
mention that?

751
00:40:41.705 --> 00:40:43.969
Yeah. You kind of did.

752
00:40:44.041 --> 00:40:45.736
I'm sorry.

753
00:40:45.810 --> 00:40:47.903
It's okay. It's okay.
I'm sorry. I'm...

754
00:40:51.148 --> 00:40:55.016
<i>Okay. So. trying on the clothes
before I told Nicole about Sienna</i>

755
00:40:55.085 --> 00:40:57.713
<i>probably wasn't the best
way to handle things.</i>

756
00:40:57.788 --> 00:41:00.723
<i>What can I say?
Sometimes. we get it wrong.</i>

757
00:41:10.267 --> 00:41:11.666
Before you hear it
from somebody else.

758
00:41:11.735 --> 00:41:14.727
I smacked an Indian's
johnson with a bar of soap today.

759
00:41:14.805 --> 00:41:16.568
Just thought
you should know.

760
00:41:16.640 --> 00:41:18.232
Haven't we done enough
to those people?

761
00:41:18.309 --> 00:41:19.742
I'm not
proud of myself.

762
00:41:19.810 --> 00:41:21.209
You come up
with anything?

763
00:41:21.278 --> 00:41:23.769
Not really. Oh. except that
two days ago.

764
00:41:23.848 --> 00:41:26.078
a three-second call
came into Santoro's house

765
00:41:26.150 --> 00:41:28.846
from a cell registered
to Richie Mastro.

766
00:41:29.687 --> 00:41:30.949
Run that by me again?

767
00:41:31.021 --> 00:41:32.249
You heard me.

768
00:41:32.323 --> 00:41:33.881
Richie Mastro.
son of Dominick Mastro.

769
00:41:33.958 --> 00:41:36.893
Don of Dons. head of the five
families called my Frankie?

770
00:41:36.961 --> 00:41:38.292
Yes. Fredo.

771
00:41:38.362 --> 00:41:39.420
You sure?

772
00:41:39.497 --> 00:41:41.089
You know. it hurts
when you doubt me.

773
00:41:41.165 --> 00:41:42.257
All right. let's go.

774
00:41:42.333 --> 00:41:43.357
Now. where?

775
00:41:43.434 --> 00:41:45.629
Frankie Nuts has got
some explaining to do.

776
00:41:45.703 --> 00:41:46.795
Do I get to play bad cop?

777
00:41:46.871 --> 00:41:48.133
Like you could.

778
00:41:48.205 --> 00:41:49.433
Oh. damn.

779
00:41:51.642 --> 00:41:53.371
What's the matter?

780
00:41:54.478 --> 00:41:57.470
Hi. Tasha. It's me. Mary.
Is your cable on yet?

781
00:41:58.249 --> 00:41:59.409
Good.

782
00:42:01.018 --> 00:42:03.851
No. we can only pay
for the basic package.

783
00:42:04.088 --> 00:42:06.113
HBO and Showtime
are extra.

784
00:42:07.057 --> 00:42:10.220
Listen. about your groceries.
something's come up.

785
00:42:11.529 --> 00:42:13.258
So. what's the book
on young Richie?

786
00:42:13.330 --> 00:42:16.788
Well. for starters. you'd have to
say he's of questionable character.

787
00:42:16.867 --> 00:42:18.164
Tossed out of Choate.
was he?

788
00:42:18.235 --> 00:42:21.830
NYPD has him under investigation
for a handful of murders.

789
00:42:21.906 --> 00:42:22.930
Mob stuff.

790
00:42:23.007 --> 00:42:24.235
Nope. Women.

791
00:42:24.308 --> 00:42:27.300
All went missing from a
Manhattan club called Cosmos.

792
00:42:27.378 --> 00:42:29.938
An establishment Richie
was known to frequent.

793
00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:32.379
And of particular interest.
a former girlfriend

794
00:42:32.449 --> 00:42:34.144
got a restraining order
against him.

795
00:42:34.218 --> 00:42:36.550
after he broke
four of her ribs.

796
00:42:36.620 --> 00:42:39.555
Then. guess what.
Two days later. she turns up.

797
00:42:39.623 --> 00:42:40.647
Hacked to bits.

798
00:42:40.724 --> 00:42:42.419
No.
Afraid so.

799
00:42:42.493 --> 00:42:45.621
Apparently. our boy's got
girl issues. and likes knives.

800
00:42:45.696 --> 00:42:48.290
So. he does Junior. then has
his jollies with the girl?

801
00:42:48.365 --> 00:42:49.389
Could be.

802
00:42:49.466 --> 00:42:50.524
And somehow.
he got Frankie's number.

803
00:42:50.601 --> 00:42:51.590
So it would seem.

804
00:42:51.669 --> 00:42:52.761
Son of a bitch.

805
00:42:52.836 --> 00:42:55.430
A week before he
testifies against Dominick.

806
00:42:55.506 --> 00:42:57.838
I'll bet you anything Frankie
was trying to broker a deal.

807
00:42:57.908 --> 00:42:58.932
You know what I think?

808
00:42:59.009 --> 00:42:59.998
What?

809
00:43:00.077 --> 00:43:03.012
I think Frankie might have
been trying to broker a deal.

810
00:43:03.080 --> 00:43:04.206
You're an idiot.

811
00:43:24.668 --> 00:43:27.501
Where are the people
who are staying here?

812
00:43:30.641 --> 00:43:33.075
Damn it. what language do you speak?

813
00:43:33.477 --> 00:43:36.139
Oh. perfect. She's deaf.
You have a pen?

814
00:43:40.551 --> 00:43:43.076
They're gone.
She doesn't know where.

815
00:43:43.887 --> 00:43:45.013
What?

816
00:43:45.756 --> 00:43:46.984
Come on.

817
00:44:05.409 --> 00:44:06.603
You calling in
a phone trace?

818
00:44:06.677 --> 00:44:09.043
That will take hours.
Get a warrant. blah. blah. blah.

819
00:44:09.113 --> 00:44:12.048
I need to find Mastro before
he finds Frankie or vice versa.

820
00:44:13.183 --> 00:44:14.650
And since when do you
know sign language?

821
00:44:14.718 --> 00:44:16.185
Apparently. I don't.

822
00:44:16.253 --> 00:44:17.242
<i>Hello.</i>

823
00:44:17.321 --> 00:44:19.084
Hello?
Is this Richie?

824
00:44:19.156 --> 00:44:20.180
You've got
to be kidding.

825
00:44:20.257 --> 00:44:21.485
<i>Yeah. who's this?</i>

826
00:44:21.558 --> 00:44:23.788
This is Nomi.

827
00:44:23.861 --> 00:44:26.125
I don't know if you remember
me and my girlfriend. Pia.

828
00:44:26.196 --> 00:44:28.721
met you at Cosmos
a few weeks ago.

829
00:44:29.166 --> 00:44:31.100
<i>Maybe. I meet a lot
of chicks. What's up?</i>

830
00:44:31.168 --> 00:44:34.626
Well. Pia and I were just
talking about how much fun it was

831
00:44:34.705 --> 00:44:38.505
to hang out with you and how much we
wanted to party with you that night.

832
00:44:38.575 --> 00:44:40.634
And Pia said we should just call
you and see what you was doing.

833
00:44:40.711 --> 00:44:42.110
No way in hell
this works.

834
00:44:42.179 --> 00:44:44.272
<i>Yeah.
Maybe some other time.</i>

835
00:44:47.985 --> 00:44:50.681
Pia. what are you doing?

836
00:44:50.821 --> 00:44:52.550
Please don't talk dirty.

837
00:44:52.623 --> 00:44:54.523
Oh. Richie.
I wish you could see this.

838
00:44:54.591 --> 00:44:55.819
Me. too.

839
00:44:55.893 --> 00:44:58.589
<i>What exactly is
Pia doing to you?</i>

840
00:44:59.530 --> 00:45:00.861
Well...

841
00:45:00.931 --> 00:45:02.626
First of all.
I'm lying on my tummy

842
00:45:02.700 --> 00:45:05.567
and I'm wearing this
real short skirt.

843
00:45:05.803 --> 00:45:07.327
And Pia's
taking her tongue

844
00:45:07.404 --> 00:45:10.134
and running it
all the way up my...

845
00:45:11.275 --> 00:45:12.367
Oh!

846
00:45:13.010 --> 00:45:14.602
Sweet mother!

847
00:45:25.723 --> 00:45:27.816
She's talking
to her mother.

848
00:45:29.059 --> 00:45:30.151
Ooh!

849
00:45:33.263 --> 00:45:37.359
Oh. Richie. I want to do
you like Pia just did me.

850
00:45:37.534 --> 00:45:40.526
Tell me where you are
and we'll come over in a cab.

851
00:45:40.604 --> 00:45:42.799
That is. if you think
you can handle both of us.

852
00:45:43.941 --> 00:45:45.431
<i>Listen. Uh. Romy...</i>

853
00:45:45.509 --> 00:45:46.498
Nomi.

854
00:45:46.577 --> 00:45:48.010
<i>Okay. Listen. Nomi.</i>

855
00:45:48.078 --> 00:45:50.171
<i>Much as I'd love to
party with you and Pia.</i>

856
00:45:50.247 --> 00:45:52.681
<i>and trust me. I got more
than enough for both of you.</i>

857
00:45:52.750 --> 00:45:54.980
<i>that's going to be an
awfully pricey cab ride.</i>

858
00:45:55.085 --> 00:45:56.143
Why's that?

859
00:45:56.220 --> 00:45:58.780
<i>Because I'm in
Albuquerque. cupcake.</i>

860
00:45:59.857 --> 00:46:01.256
Albuquerque?

861
00:46:01.358 --> 00:46:02.382
Unbelievable.

862
00:46:02.459 --> 00:46:04.984
How funny. Some guy just
invited me out there

863
00:46:05.062 --> 00:46:07.462
for some balloon festival.
whatever the hell that is.

864
00:46:07.531 --> 00:46:09.021
<i>No kidding.</i>

865
00:46:09.099 --> 00:46:11.192
Yeah.
Some coincidence. right?

866
00:46:11.268 --> 00:46:13.964
Hey. Are there any decent
places to stay out there?

867
00:46:14.037 --> 00:46:17.131
<i>Yeah. they got one really
nice resort just out of town.</i>

868
00:46:17.207 --> 00:46:19.971
<i>Golf. spa. the whole deal.</i>

869
00:46:20.043 --> 00:46:22.170
That sounds... Uh-oh.

870
00:46:22.246 --> 00:46:25.181
I think my husband
just got home.

871
00:46:30.354 --> 00:46:32.254
Honey. I'm home.

872
00:46:32.756 --> 00:46:36.453
Mother Mary and Joseph.
What's going on here?

873
00:46:37.294 --> 00:46:41.526
Where are your panties?
You bad. bad girl.

874
00:46:43.967 --> 00:46:46.435
I've got to go.
I'll call you back.

875
00:46:47.704 --> 00:46:49.262
That's just...

876
00:46:50.007 --> 00:46:51.133
Nomi?

877
00:46:52.109 --> 00:46:53.736
<i>From Showgirls.</i>

878
00:46:54.611 --> 00:46:55.805
Sweet.

879
00:47:11.328 --> 00:47:12.590
I'll take that
for you. ma'am.

880
00:47:12.663 --> 00:47:13.994
Keep it close.

881
00:47:26.176 --> 00:47:27.268
Is this guy
staying here?

882
00:47:27.344 --> 00:47:29.972
We don't give out
information about our guests.

883
00:47:30.047 --> 00:47:33.039
Okay. So. you won't mind if my
friend and I start banging on doors.

884
00:47:33.116 --> 00:47:35.414
telling your guests there's
a serial killer staying here.

885
00:47:35.485 --> 00:47:37.043
Come on. Marshall.

886
00:47:37.120 --> 00:47:39.111
Excuse me.

887
00:47:41.725 --> 00:47:44.387
That's Mr. Martell
in suite 1014.

888
00:47:44.461 --> 00:47:45.928
And he tips very well.

889
00:47:45.996 --> 00:47:47.020
Thank you.

890
00:47:53.303 --> 00:47:54.531
Who is it?

891
00:47:54.605 --> 00:47:56.197
Room service.
Mr. Martell.

892
00:47:56.273 --> 00:47:58.798
I have a fruit basket.
compliments of the hotel.

893
00:47:58.876 --> 00:48:01.071
Leave it by the door.

894
00:48:02.412 --> 00:48:05.040
And a bottle of
Dom Perignon.

895
00:48:05.115 --> 00:48:07.640
I'm not allowed to
leave it outside.

896
00:48:07.818 --> 00:48:09.547
All right. hold on.

897
00:48:09.820 --> 00:48:11.481
Pain in the ass.

898
00:48:13.090 --> 00:48:14.182
Freeze!

899
00:48:20.063 --> 00:48:21.189
Don't even fart.

900
00:48:21.265 --> 00:48:23.893
My wallet's on the bar.
Take whatever you want.

901
00:48:23.967 --> 00:48:26.993
We're not here to rob you. you
stupid hump. We're U.S. Marshals.

902
00:48:27.070 --> 00:48:28.264
I didn't do nothing.

903
00:48:28.338 --> 00:48:30.829
Oh. yeah?
Isn't that cute?

904
00:48:30.908 --> 00:48:32.500
That ain't mine.

905
00:48:38.982 --> 00:48:40.176
Where's Frankie?

906
00:48:40.250 --> 00:48:41.649
Frankie who?

907
00:48:41.818 --> 00:48:43.445
Santoro.
Where is he?

908
00:48:43.520 --> 00:48:46.216
Frankie Nuts?
How the hell should I know?

909
00:48:46.723 --> 00:48:48.418
What are you. a nun?

910
00:48:48.492 --> 00:48:49.891
Quit screwing with me.

911
00:48:49.960 --> 00:48:51.222
I know your father
sent you to kill him.

912
00:48:51.295 --> 00:48:52.853
Now. tell me where he is or so help me.

913
00:48:52.930 --> 00:48:55.194
I will feed this ear
to my mother's poodles.

914
00:48:55.265 --> 00:48:56.323
I thought
they were Shih Tzus.

915
00:48:56.400 --> 00:48:57.731
Focus. Marshall.

916
00:49:01.171 --> 00:49:02.638
Where the hell are you?

917
00:49:02.706 --> 00:49:05.072
I thought I told you
to stay put.

918
00:49:05.442 --> 00:49:08.605
No. it isn't all right.
Stay there. I'm coming over.

919
00:49:09.046 --> 00:49:12.174
Something's come up.
Be a dear and take him in.

920
00:49:12.316 --> 00:49:16.013
Yes. honey. Shall I pick up your
dry cleaning while I'm at it?

921
00:49:16.119 --> 00:49:17.984
Take me in? What for?

922
00:49:18.622 --> 00:49:20.715
For ending an interrogatory
with a preposition.

923
00:49:20.791 --> 00:49:23.225
Hey. that's
a six-dollar candy bar.

924
00:49:23.293 --> 00:49:25.284
Put these on and shut up.

925
00:49:25.796 --> 00:49:27.058
Easy.

926
00:49:44.247 --> 00:49:47.114
Idiots. Can't even stick
where I tell them.

927
00:49:47.384 --> 00:49:49.318
They're like children.

928
00:49:49.553 --> 00:49:51.248
Children with ADD.

929
00:49:52.089 --> 00:49:54.148
Damn it.
Tasha's groceries.

930
00:49:58.462 --> 00:49:59.588
Hey.

931
00:50:00.831 --> 00:50:01.923
Let me explain
something to you.

932
00:50:01.999 --> 00:50:04.194
When I tell you to stay
someplace. you stay there.

933
00:50:04.267 --> 00:50:06.701
You can't just change
locations without telling me.

934
00:50:06.770 --> 00:50:08.169
I don't have time to
go chasing

935
00:50:08.238 --> 00:50:10.638
all over hell and high
water looking for you.

936
00:50:10.707 --> 00:50:12.868
This goes for you. too.
Felicia.

937
00:50:12.943 --> 00:50:14.968
I needed to
light a candle.

938
00:50:17.547 --> 00:50:20.380
Listen. I know you two
are hurting. But this...

939
00:50:20.450 --> 00:50:22.850
This is not how
the program works.

940
00:50:23.987 --> 00:50:25.249
We checked into
the Marriott.

941
00:50:25.322 --> 00:50:27.756
The other place was
too depressing.

942
00:50:28.992 --> 00:50:31.085
The bedspread had stains.

943
00:50:36.133 --> 00:50:39.125
How does Richie Mastro
have your phone number?

944
00:50:39.970 --> 00:50:41.062
What?

945
00:50:41.405 --> 00:50:43.600
You heard me. He called your
house two days ago and hung up.

946
00:50:43.673 --> 00:50:45.766
Like he was
checking the number.

947
00:50:45.842 --> 00:50:47.742
I know I didn't give
it to him. So. who did?

948
00:50:47.811 --> 00:50:50.541
It wasn't me. I haven't
contacted anybody.

949
00:50:54.084 --> 00:50:55.244
Oh. God.

950
00:50:55.318 --> 00:50:56.512
What?

951
00:50:57.020 --> 00:50:59.716
Oh. God.
Did I get Frankie killed?

952
00:50:59.790 --> 00:51:01.917
What? Tell us what you
did. Felicia. You stupid...

953
00:51:03.427 --> 00:51:05.156
What happened? Have you
been talking to someone?

954
00:51:05.228 --> 00:51:07.594
No. No. No. I swear.

955
00:51:07.664 --> 00:51:10.326
Not on the phone.
On the Internet.

956
00:51:10.400 --> 00:51:12.891
Me and Cathy. we've been e
- mailing each other.

957
00:51:12.969 --> 00:51:14.800
But I never told her
where we were

958
00:51:14.871 --> 00:51:16.771
and I didn't give her our
number. I swear on my life.

959
00:51:16.840 --> 00:51:17.864
Who's Cathy?

960
00:51:17.941 --> 00:51:19.272
It's Mastro's wife.

961
00:51:19.342 --> 00:51:21.902
They been friends
since grade school.

962
00:51:21.978 --> 00:51:22.967
What did I do?

963
00:51:23.046 --> 00:51:26.447
He probably found out
and he tapped our ISP.

964
00:51:26.516 --> 00:51:30.316
Felicia. listen to me. We don't know
that Mastro had anything to do with this.

965
00:51:30.387 --> 00:51:31.786
Where is he?

966
00:51:32.022 --> 00:51:34.286
Hey. Don't do this
to yourself.

967
00:51:35.025 --> 00:51:37.619
Until we know for sure
what happened.

968
00:51:37.694 --> 00:51:40.288
you can't assume this has
any connection to you.

969
00:51:40.363 --> 00:51:41.489
Look.

970
00:51:41.798 --> 00:51:45.529
You tell me where that son of
a bitch. Mastro. is right now.

971
00:51:49.072 --> 00:51:50.471
Do we have anything
to hold him on?

972
00:51:50.540 --> 00:51:51.632
Tampering with a witness.

973
00:51:51.708 --> 00:51:54.108
Maybe hampering
a prosecution.

974
00:51:54.177 --> 00:51:55.201
What about the murder?

975
00:51:55.278 --> 00:51:57.508
Unless something turns up.
he walks in 48 hours.

976
00:51:57.581 --> 00:51:59.981
Yeah. yeah.
That's what I figured.

977
00:52:00.283 --> 00:52:04.117
So. I returned the perfume.

978
